d the poison suitable for your level? Or if you have alot of money use one thats 250 and still get the same gain ratio? Thanks in advance.<br>
<br>
Slinker <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukostaman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KostaMan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://kostaman.8k.com/ring20.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/24/01 9:02:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skill Gains faster on poison close to trival or no?</span><hr size=1> I have heard that you get more increases if you work on stuff around same skill lvl as yours, but i have not personal tried this.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: Check our sig rules. - ShadowCross</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushadowcross.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowcross</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/4/01 4:31:25 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umenamino.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Menamino </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/25/01 4:24:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skill Gains faster on poison close to trival or no?</span><hr size=1> I can confirm that skill level goes up faster if you use poisons around the skill level youre at. About a week ago (when I was at 146 skill or so I believe) I bought a ton of ingredients in FV to try and make Spirit of Sloth (40 attempts). I failed 38 times, made 2, and had no skill ups. Then I switched back to Calcium Rot (trivial at like 17<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and I got to 166 in no time. Hope it helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uduloktherogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dulok the Rogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/28/01 11:25:02 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dulok.twu.net/dulok_head.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skill Gains faster on poison close to trival or no?</span><hr size=1> I think it is suppose to be this way but from my point of view it seemed I got points faster when I was making tier 4 at 50 skill then I do now, however +200 is alot slower then standard skill increases <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21751">Dulok - 60 Assassin</a>
<br>
<a href="http://www.hneguild.com">Heaven and Earth</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukeltarinstormshadow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keltarin Stormshadow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/28/01 11:36:55 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skill Gains faster on poison close to trival or no?</span><hr size=1> This is conjecture from my experiences, but I've done a lot of tradeskills and I find I'm more likely to skill up on a success than a failure.  This implies that it would be better to work on stuff close to trivial, since you're more likely to succeed more often.<br>
<br>
This theory is hard to test though due to the streakyness of the RNG and due to the fact that as you skill up it becomes harder to skill up again.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: Check our sig rules. - ShadowCross</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushadowcross.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowcross</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/4/01 4:31:48 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upanamah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Panamah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/2/01 7:02:40 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://nmcs.com/kingscourt/images/panamah.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skill Gains faster on poison close to trival or no?</span><hr size=1> I'm reasonably sure this is true, but I have nothing empirical.  I noticed it for baking.  When I made fish rolls as a low level baker, I got few skill ups.  When I made fish fillets, which trivial much lower, my skill ups came faster. <p><a href="http://nmcs.com/kingscourt/images/mytrio.jpg">The Three Sopranos</a><br><font size=1><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8428">Panamah,<em> 55th level peculator</em></a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8188"><font size=1>Electrae, <em>High Priestess of Tunare</em></a>
<br>Wysteria Plushfoot, <em>druid slave to those other two hussies</em>
</em></font><br><a href="http://nmcs.com/kingscourt"><b>King's Court</b></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhokksin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hokksin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/2/01 8:58:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skill Gains faster on poison close to trival or no?</span><hr size=1>   I can only remember 1 time I got a skill up with a failure.  I know that does not prove anything but that is what happened in my case.<br>
<br>
<br>
Hokksin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushalysa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shalysa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/5/01 2:45:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skill Gains faster on poison close to trival or no?</span><hr size=1> This is all pure conjecture, since Verant hasn't seen fit to fill us in on details such as these.  But I have personally at least mastered every tradeskill with one character or another (Ok, except tinkering, its only in the 80's right now ;)) and I spend a lotta time on eqtraders.com.<br>
<br>
This topic comes up on occasion, and although there is always a lot of speculation, the most commonly expressed belief seems to be that there is a "sweet spot" for skill gains -- probably somewhere between 5 and 20 under the trivial of your current attempted product.  Once you get fairly close to trivial (i.e. within 5 points), skill gains seem to taper off.  <br>
<br>
Coincidence?  Luck?  Imagination?  A by-product of the streaky nature of the RNG?  I don't know, maybe.  But I definitely seem to learn skills faster when I actually follow a progression of increasingly more difficult to craft items, moving to the next higher one once I get close to trivial as skill gains dry up.  YMMV =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showMessage?topicID=2159.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.showMessage?topicID=2157.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.emailToFriend?topicID=2147.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.threadControl?topicID=2147.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2147.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselaboratory.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2147.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafo